Then bring Más Agave Premium Hard Seltzer home to admire for yourself by heading to our beer finder at the link in our bio.

Starting today, we’ll be releasing weekly beer education videos to help you pass the time and hopefully, help you come out of this with some new beer knowledge.

node.text:
It’s the weekend. Time to slip on your evening robe and slippers, get out a bottle of Velvet Rush and treat yourself.⁠
⁠
This barrel-aged Imperial Brown Ale is making its way to shelves as we speak. Head to the link in our bio to see if it’s arrived near you! #foundersbrewing

node.text:
If you try really hard we bet you can smell this photo.⁠
⁠
Only the freshest hops make it into our Harvest Ale every year, and the wet hopping process releases some intense and amazing aromas into the brewhouse. ⁠
⁠
Get ready for the release of Harvest Ale exclusively at our taprooms as part of the Mothership Series on October 6. Head to the link in our bio to learn more!⁠
#foundersbrewing

node.text:
We’ve said it before and we’ll say it again: we love seeing how much our fans enjoy what we make.

It just so happens that some love our beer so much that they stage entire photoshoots for it. Thanks to our friend @adeptbeerlens for this stunning KBS shot! #foundersbrewing

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Founders Brewing Co. on September 07, 2021 tagging @madcapcoffee, and @leafmeco. May be an image of bottle.

node.text:
It’s time for another round of #CraftedinMI Collaboration Series beers – this time featuring @madcapcoffee of Grand Rapids and @leafmeco of Detroit!
 
First up we have Madcask Hazy IPA coming in at 6.6% ABV. Heavily inspired by the popular Painkiller cocktail, the addition of cascara (the dried fruit of the coffee cherry), orange, pineapple and coconut with citrusy and tropical hops will have you setting sail for your secret island hideaway. 
 
Next is Align Me Gruit Style Ale, which incorporates a bouquet of botanicals and herbs to represent each of the seven Chakras. Supported by spicy ginger and hibiscus flowers, this beer clocks in at 5.8% ABV and is a rare gem you won’t want to miss.
 
Both beers are extremely limited and will be available exclusively in our taprooms in 750mL bottles and on draft. Madcask Hazy IPA will release on September 24 and Align Me Gruit Style Ale will release on September 17. Both of our partners will be in their respective taprooms on release day, so head to the link in our bio for more info! #foundersbrewing

“What do you mean they don’t have flies on the menu here?!”⁠
⁠
Thanks to our friends Abe and Lucinda for this AMAZING All Day IPA sand sculpture. There’s nothing we enjoy more than seeing how much our fans love our beer. #foundersbrewing

Just because summer is coming to a close doesn’t mean you can’t enjoy the last little bit of it with good friends and great beer. Track down your favorite beers at the link in our bio. #foundersbrewing

node.text:
It's never too early to think about how you'll be spending your weekend! Let us help with a recipe that's good for breakfast or happy hour – Beergarita style. ⁠
⁠
All you need to do is salt your rim, throw in some ice and add: ⁠
⁠
-A shot of tequila⁠
-A shot of orange juice⁠
-A splash of lime juice⁠
-Top off with Unraveled IPA⁠
⁠
You can doctor this cocktail up however you want. In fact, throw in some suggestions in the comments! #foundersbrewing

node.text:
DATE POSTPONED: We’re bringing our #CraftedinMI series to life by debuting a Crafted in Michigan Market presented by @sixwaysmarkets at our Grand Rapids taproom!
 
This FREE, all-ages outdoor artist market will take place in our parking lot (on the corner of Wealthy and Grandville) and feature a variety of crafters and makers. We’ll also have special food offerings, roaming music by @nicholasjamesthomasma and lots of refreshing beer (obviously).
 
Expect to see vendors like @arsenalhandicraft, @happypeoplehike, @plutomonday, @anycolour_you_like, @beesinthed, @losttimberwoodwork and many more, so mark your calendars for September 11 & 12 for a weekend full of Michigan made art! More info at the link in bio. #foundersbrewing
